Wow, you're pretty fucking ignorant if you can't see the logic in all of these posts telling you why you're an idiot and why you're wrong.  Swearing an slang don't take anything away from whether or not an argument is valid, but again, you have to make believe that they do so you can ignore the logic attached to them. Some people like to actually be expressive with what they write. I for one write the same way I talk, and I swear alot. That doesn't mean I'm wrong....cock sucker.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Btw organization is the only means to run things. Without organization we'd be in trouble. Case in point, look at third world countries. That's how Drinal is atm, no organization and nothing but greedy people who try to bully the smaller players and not allow them to become stronger. I can't help but think how rediculous your notions are that free for alls are the way to live, that's absolutely obsurd, it doesn't work in the real world what makes you even think it would in a game. That's just an excuse and ignorance to the law is not acceptable.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Actually, you're wrong (big shock there). Organization is best achieved through individual actions governed by lose rules (PnP anyone?). The best current example is the US. It's no coincidence that the country that allows the most individual freedom is also the economicly strongest. Show me the organization that is better at expressing and fullfilling the ideas and wants of every individual than the individual is. You're going to have a hell of a time doing that, why? Because what you say in your &quot;arguments&quot; is totally irrational. Oh, and try to find me a third world country where absolutely ALL factors concerning the way it works and is run are the same as EQ. Seriously, do you think before you write this shit? Oh and if you think that people act the same way in RL that they do in EQ or on these boards, you're in for another shocker, and again, just shows how ignorant you are.<br>
<br>
Hell, an officer from the guild you are trying to &quot;defend&quot; even came on here and said he doesn't agree with you.<br>
